Subject: [PATCH 1789/2508] ASoC: Intel: Add a machine driver for BXT-P IVI
 Head Unit

commit 57c1f6666e4ab47a0ef000de306725236585b262 from
https://github.com/01org/linux-apollolake-i

The HU in IVI uses a bluetooth codec for playback and capture
of audio voice call data. The codec is substitued with a
Dummy Codec driver until the suitable codec is identified.

Related Changes for Makefile and Kconfig have been added.

